response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Reverse String Words\", \"description\": \"Write a function `reverse_words` that takes a string and reverses the order of its words. The function should preserve the original casing, punctuation, and word boundaries.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef reverse_words(s: str) -> str:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `s` (str): A string containing one or more words separated by spaces.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns a string with the order of its words reversed, while preserving original casing, punctuation, and word boundaries.\\n\", \"code\": \"import re\\n\\ndef reverse_words(s: str) -> str:\\n    # Split the input string into words using regex to preserve punctuation and spacing\\n    words = re.findall(r'[\\w\\'\\\"-]+', s)\\n    # Reverse the list of words\\n    reversed_words = words[::-1]\\n    # Join the reversed list of words back into a single string\\n    return ' '.join(reversed_words)\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert reverse_words(\\\"Hello world\\\") == \\\"world Hello\\\"\", \"assert reverse_words(\\\"A man, a plan, a canal, Panama!\\\") == \\\"Panama! a canal, a plan, a man,\\\"\", \"assert reverse_words(\\\"The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog.\\\") == \\\"dog. lazy the over jumps fox brown quick The\\\"\"] }"
